  "body": "About #20172\r\nSeems like I have found the reason where all these *big.int are held, they are likely being held by the BalanceChange journalEntry.\r\n\r\nfunc (self *stateObject) SetBalance(amount *big.Int) {\r\n\tself.db.journal.append(balanceChange{\r\n\t\taccount: &self.address,\r\n\t\tprev:    new(big.Int).Set(self.data.Balance),   //this is the cause\r\n\t})\r\n\tself.setBalance(amount)\r\n}\r\n\r\nOur test is simply lots of transfer txs, without any contract execution. Each transaction tx just adds one wei to the to account.\r\n\r\nI am wondering, if we need to keep those journals in memory forever, should we have some cleaning mechanism, or set a max length to it?\r\n",
